rs and I whole-heartedly agree that it is worth going to the fat side, Luke.</p><p>Delicious&#8230;perhaps a new favorite as far as cream sauces go.  It worked in perfect harmony with my already flavorfully seasoned crawdads, shrimp and andouille sausage.  Thank you!</p></div></div></li><li class="post pingback"><p>Pingback: <a href='http://knitterinthekitchen.com/2007/10/01/this-week/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Knitter in the Kitchen &raquo; This Week</a></p></li><li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-74420"><div id="comment-74420"> <img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/67c973b956d048ef6d1fa310c694626e?s=32&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fsteamykitchen.com%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fsteamykitchen2010%2Fimages%2Fgravatar.png%3Fs%3D32&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' /><div class="reply"> <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/73-pasta-with-creamy-cajun-sauce.html?replytocom=74420#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-74420", "74420", "respond", "73")'>Reply</a></div><div class="commentmeta"><strong>Rexey</strong> &#8212; 3/14/09 @ <a href="#comment-74420">5:03 pm</a></div><div class="comment-body"><p>The link to chicken base seems dead.<br /> What is it?</p><p>One of my better received dishes is just a simple twirly pasta dish with sun dried tomato pesto and a good sausage.  I&#8217;d like to try swapping the pesto for this and see what happens. 1 pint of cream?  We&#8217;ll probably be sound asleep 30mins after eating it.</p></div></div></li><li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-84156"><div id="comment-84156"> <img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/e9f57e39666912fc008bfea3658bcc95?s=32&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fsteamykitchen.com%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fsteamykitchen2010%2Fimages%2Fgravatar.png%3Fs%3D32&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' /><div class="reply"> <a class='comment-reply-link' href='/73-pasta-with-creamy-cajun-sauce.html?reply